HM Treasury







Publication scheme






    Each government department has a publication scheme, which makes information available about how it works and spends its budget.
  







Types of information we publish
Under section 19 of the Freedom of Information Act all government departments such as the Treasury have to adopt a Publication Scheme approved by the Information Commissioner.
It means that we should make information available about:

who we are and what we do
what we spend and how we spend it
what our priorities are and how we are doing
how we make decisions

How to get information
We usually publish information that we are required to provide on this website. If you can’t find the information you need on this site, then you can make a Freedom of Information (FOI) request.
Our annual report is also a main source for information about HM Treasury, and budget and pre-budget publications cover important economic analysis.








    Contents








Help us improve GOV.UK





Don’t include personal or financial information like your National Insurance number or credit card details.
